                    <statement_number>3.235</statement_number>
                    <statement>The representative of the United Kingdom delivered the following statement:</statement>
                </statement_info>
                <!--STATEMENT CONTENT-->
                <statement_content>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 3.236-->
                    <paragraph id="3.236">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>The UK would like to start by commending the efforts by the Facilitator, and in particular, all of her leadership and guidance throughout this process. The UK aligns with the statement made by Switzerland, on behalf of the co-sponsors. The UK is pleased to co-sponsor communication WT/GC/W/909. Renewal of the moratorium will preserve the foundation of global digital trade and provide certainty for consumers and businesses around the world.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 3.237-->
                    <paragraph id="3.237">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>We do not have to wait for the Ministerial to deliver an outcome. Renewing the moratorium is something that we can and should do right here. We welcome the ACP Group's recent communication seeking to extend the moratorium. Over 100 Members are now calling for the moratorium to be extended at this time. We urge Members to join with a growing consensus – to get this done before the Ministerial.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
