                    <statement>The representative of China delivered the following statement:</statement>
                </statement_info>
                <!--STATEMENT CONTENT-->
                <statement_content>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 3.295-->
                    <paragraph id="3.295">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>China thanks the Facilitator for her report and tireless efforts in facilitating the dedicated discussions. Under her capable leadership and with Members' proactive engagement, China is pleased to see the reinvigoration of the Work Programme on E-Commerce.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 3.296-->
                    <paragraph id="3.296">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>China appreciates the WTO Secretariat's coordination and hard work on launching the joint report on Digital Trade for Development. China recognizes the positive role that this report will play in facilitating Members' further discussions, as it provides a common analytical basis and avoids citing different reports with polarized findings.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 3.297-->
                    <paragraph id="3.297">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>On the draft Ministerial Decision, our thanks go to the proponents for their respective proposals. China supports a balanced E-commerce outcome at MC13, to help developing Members harness opportunities arising from digital economy and respond to the calls of business community. To this end, the Ministerial Decision should include the following elements. First, Members should intensify post-MC13 work under the Work Programme, especially with a continued focus on its development dimension. Second, the moratorium should be extended to MC14. Third, Members should further discuss the scope, definition and impact of the moratorium.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                </statement_content>
                <!--STATEMENT INFO-->
                <statement_info>
                    <statement_number>3.298</statement_number>
                    <statement>The representative of Egypt delivered the following statement:</statement>
                </statement_info>
                <!--STATEMENT CONTENT-->
                <statement_content>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 3.299-->
                    <paragraph id="3.299">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>We express our gratitude to the Facilitator for her report and her unwavering dedication to supporting our efforts during the focused discussions on E-commerce. We also extend our appreciation to South Africa for the insightful presentation on the submission contained in WT/GC/W/910 regarding the challenges related to digital industrialization in developing countries. Additionally, we acknowledge the draft ministerial decision in WT/GC/W/911. Our thanks are also extended to the proponents of the draft ministerial decision outlined in WT/GC/W/909. We acknowledge the ACP Group submission.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 3.300-->
                    <paragraph id="3.300">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>Some of the challenges faced by small and developing countries businesses in the digital market - as highlighted in the South African submission - include the unfair advantage that global tech platforms have due to their access to cheap venture capital and global profit streams. These challenges, coupled with others, hinder the participation of developing countries in the market, such as the insufficient digital infrastructure and internet access, limited technical expertise and resources for businesses and regulatory bodies and more. We will engage with our colleagues from South Africa to explore the ideas contained in the submission and see to how to implement the proposed remedial actions in practice.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 3.301-->
                    <paragraph id="3.301">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>We firmly believe that the WTO should play a pivotal role in offering effective solutions to the challenges faced by developing countries, including the least developed countries (LDCs), as they strive to achieve digital industrialization and increase their global engagement in e-commerce. This includes addressing the digital divide both among and within countries.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 3.302-->
                    <paragraph id="3.302">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>We seriously consider South Africa's proposed elements in the draft ministerial decision in WT/GC/W/911, including the establishment of a fund designed to support initiatives that address the digital divide, enhance technical capacity, and improve visibility and discoverability among consumers.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 3.303-->
                    <paragraph id="3.303">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>Additionally, we emphasize the importance of continuing the reinvigoration of work under the work programme on e-commerce after MC13 as emphasized by Ministers during the recent Mini-Ministerial meeting held last Monday.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 3.304-->
                    <paragraph id="3.304">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>Initiating discussions and fostering constructive engagement on promoting technology transfer in developing countries and LDCs within the context of e-commerce is crucial to help addressing global development challenges.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 3.305-->
                    <paragraph id="3.305">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>Conducting E-readiness assessment in individual countries with a particular focus on the developmental aspect is imperative, this complements our efforts to reinvigorate the work program. In this regard we highlight the significance of collaborating with other relevant international organizations, particularly UNCTAD and ITC, as far as e-readiness assessment is concerned.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 3.306-->
                    <paragraph id="3.306">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>Finally, we reiterate that the moratorium should not be renewed automatically. The moratorium should be subject to further analysis concerning its scope and definition. An assessment based on a cost-benefit analysis should be conducted for all potential scenarios, including the termination of the moratorium, its extension, or retention. These analyses should inform our final decision.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                </statement_content>
                <!--STATEMENT INFO-->
                <statement_info>
