                    <statement>The representative of Australia delivered the following statement:</statement>
                </statement_info>
                <!--STATEMENT CONTENT-->
                <statement_content>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 3.360-->
                    <paragraph id="3.360">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>We also thank the Facilitator for her leadership and report today. We support continuing discussions in the Work Programme on trade-related topics to allow developing countries and LDCs to better engage and benefit from e-commerce and the digital economy. On the e-commerce moratorium for Australia, it is a clear, that there is a growing consensus among Members that one of the most damaging things at MC13 could be to let the moratorium lapse. We therefore must see it renewed, ideally before the Conference.</t>
