                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 3.387-->
                    <paragraph id="3.387">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>I wanted to add on top of that, Fiji mentioned the digital divide and the need for developing countries being supported to bridge this divide. I mentioned earlier there is an ongoing programme to do that. We started in Africa with the World Bank that wants to invest in developing countries to do hardware, and we will work with them on software. We had a meeting. They wanted to start in African region. We have asked African countries that wanted to participate to volunteer. We have some countries – Kenya, Rwanda, Benin, Cote d'Ivoire, Ghana, Togo, Nigeria and Mauritius – who have all volunteered to be part of this. As we speak, DDG Zhang is not here, he is on mission with the World Bank in Rwanda, followed by Benin and Cote d'Ivoire, on this work. Sometimes action is important. I hope, from where we are in Africa, we can move to Latin America, the Pacific and all over the world, if this programme succeeds. So, there is some hope for developing countries that are trying to bridge the digital divide, and whatever decision is made they will be able to benefit because they will have the appropriate infrastructure when this is done.</t>
