                <!--STATEMENT INFO-->
                <statement_info>
                    <statement_number>4.30</statement_number>
                    <statement>The representative of Sri Lanka delivered the following statement:</statement>
                </statement_info>
                <!--STATEMENT CONTENT-->
                <statement_content>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 4.31-->
                    <paragraph id="4.31">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>My delegation wishes to extend our appreciation to the CTD Chairperson for its report on Small Economies. Despite repeated emphasis on our commitment to the Work Programme on Small Economies to adopt specific measures that would facilitate the fuller integration of SVEs into the multilateral trading system, as indicated in the Secretariat report (WT/COMTD/SE/W/45), SVEs participation in global merchandise trade has increased mere 0.05% from 2010 to 2019.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 4.32-->
                    <paragraph id="4.32">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>Therefore, there is a need for further work in order to fully achieve the mandate of the Doha Ministerial Declaration as indicated in the Chair's report. As highlighted at many forums, SVEs are diverse and dynamic on their own problems as well as solutions which could possibly go beyond the scope of the WTO. Therefore, external collaborations are very important, as indicated under the draft declaration.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 4.33-->
                    <paragraph id="4.33">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>The draft declaration emphasizes the area of e-commerce and digital ecosystem, transparent supply chains for food security issues, trade costs, and last but not least how to integrate climate change adaptation and mitigation policies into the trade policies of SVEs. These are the areas, where wider WTO membership is deliberated upon, where SVEs should also benefit from these multilateral processes.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                </statement_content>
                <!--STATEMENT INFO-->
                <statement_info>
