                    <statement_number>4.39</statement_number>
                    <statement>The representative of Fiji, on behalf of the Pacific Group, delivered the following statement:</statement>
                </statement_info>
                <!--STATEMENT CONTENT-->
                <statement_content>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 4.40-->
                    <paragraph id="4.40">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>The Pacific Group thanks the CTD Chair for his report and for his leadership. Our Group also supports the SVEs statement and align with ACP Group statement. SVEs have structural vulnerabilities owing to their smallness, isolation and limited capacities that result in high trade costs and thereby make them uncompetitive in world markets. These are compounded by the impact of climate change. We therefore commend the work undertaken in the Dedicated Session including experience sharing to address the trade challenges of SVEs and also to identify opportunities to address these challenges.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 4.41-->
                    <paragraph id="4.41">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>The Pacific Group supports the draft Decision at MC13 to extend the Work Programme on Small Economies. In particular, to continue the work on identifying opportunities and addressing the challenges to digitalization in SVEs, ensuring access to reliable and transparent supply chains including for food security and reducing non-tariff barriers to reduce trade costs; and exploring how to integrate trade-related climate change adaption and mitigation into the trade policies of small economies. We therefore urge Members to support this work going forward, which must deliver on the mandate, that is, to frame responses to the trade challenges faced by small vulnerable economies.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 4.42-->
