                <!--STATEMENT INFO-->
                <statement_info>
                    <statement_number>4.46</statement_number>
                    <statement>The representative of the United Kingdom delivered the following statement:</statement>
                </statement_info>
                <!--STATEMENT CONTENT-->
                <statement_content>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 4.47-->
                    <paragraph id="4.47">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>The United Kingdom welcomes the work that the Dedicated Session on Small Economies has taken forward throughout this year and thanks the chair for his leadership and support. We are pleased to have agreed language on a draft Ministerial Decision ahead of MC13. This will commit us to work on future digital trade, resilient supply chains especially around food security and climate change adaptation and mitigation. All of this will be necessary if we are going to be able to support the most vulnerable countries going forward. </t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 4.48-->
                    <paragraph id="4.48">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>Finally, whilst I have the floor, I wanted to quickly update Members to say that today the UK's Minister for Development deposited the UK's instrument of acceptance to the WTO's Fisheries Agreement and formally ratified the treaty, and I am particularly pleased to say that we have pledged to contribute up to GBP 1 million towards the Fish Fund, so we are very pleased to see the UK's flag in the map in the atrium and we are very much committed to intensifying the negotiations on phase 2 when we get started in the New Year.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                </statement_content>
                <!--STATEMENT INFO-->
                <statement_info>
                    <statement_number>4.49</statement_number>
                    <statement>The representative of Mauritius delivered the following statement:</statement>
                </statement_info>
                <!--STATEMENT CONTENT-->
                <statement_content>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 4.50-->
                    <paragraph id="4.50">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>Turning to Small Economies Chair, I thank the CTD Chair for his continued efforts to advance the issue of Small Economies. I also thank Guatemala for introducing this document on behalf of the SVEs and to which Mauritius fully subscribes. We recall that earlier this year, the Secretariat produced a very valuable document on the situation of small economies which made a significant difference by giving direction to the discussions. I thank the Secretariat for this.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 4.51-->
                    <paragraph id="4.51">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>The decision on small economies dates far back to 1998, some 25 years ago and since then, many new challenges have arisen for small economies. We look forward to the adoption of this decision by the General Council and its referral to MC13 with the hope that we can have more concrete decisions for small economies by MC14.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                </statement_content>
                <!--STATEMENT INFO-->
                <statement_info>
                    <statement_number>4.52</statement_number>
