                            <p>
                                <t>We would like to join others in thanking the CTD Chair for his tireless work in advancing the work of the Committee's dedicated sessions, including the Work Programme on Small Economies.  We also wish to thank the delegation of Guatemala for its leadership as group coordinator, and endorse the statement made by Ambassador Pérez. We very much welcome the consensus reached on the Work Programme's ministerial decision, which has taken into account discussion on areas of the utmost importance to small economies, such as e-commerce and digitalization, and supply chains for small economies in the light of food security challenges. We believe that, through this important decision, Ministers are renewing their commitment to ensuring that all Members work towards the fuller integration of small economies into world trade.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
