        <!--AGENDA-->
        <agenda>
            <!--AGENDA ITEM, HEADING-->
            <agenda_item>
                <agenda_item_number>5</agenda_item_number>
                <p>
                    <t>THE DEVELOPMENT ASSISTANCE ASPECTS OF COTTON - PERIODIC REPORT BY THE DIRECTOR-GENERAL (WT/GC/260 – WT/CFMC/DG/10 – WT/MIN(24)/1)</t>
                </p>
            </agenda_item>
            <!--OPENING-->
            <opening>
                <!--OPENING, PARAGRAPH 5.1-->
                <p>
                    <t>The Chairperson said that in 2004, the General Council had instructed the Secretariat to continue to work with the development community and to provide the Council with periodic reports on the development assistance aspects of the Cotton Initiative. The Council had also instructed the Director-General to consult with the relevant international organizations, including the Bretton Woods Institutions, the FAO and the ITC, to direct effectively existing programmes and any additional resources towards development of the economies where cotton has vital importance.  She further noted that the Bali and Nairobi Decisions reaffirmed this mandate and invited the Director-General to continue to provide periodic reports.</t>
                </p>
            </opening>
            <!--STATEMENT SECTION-->
            <statements>
                <!--STATEMENT INFO-->
                <statement_info>
                    <statement_number>5.2</statement_number>
                    <statement>The Director-General delivered the following statement:</statement>
                </statement_info>
                <!--STATEMENT CONTENT-->
                <statement_content>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 5.3-->
                    <paragraph id="5.3">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>I am pleased to introduce the Tenth Periodic Report on the Development Assistance aspects of Cotton, which was circulated on 30 November 2023 in document WT/GC/260.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 5.4-->
                    <paragraph id="5.4">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>Cotton is a critical issue to some of the most vulnerable and marginalized people of the world - For the WTO it is vital and delivering on it is long overdue.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 5.5-->
                    <paragraph id="5.5">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>On cotton development assistance, I am pleased to observe that, since the last Periodic Report in June 2022 and thanks to the dynamism of the C-4 and the positive response by the development community, we have made some remarkable progress.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 5.6-->
                    <paragraph id="5.6">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>Allow me to share some tangible progress since my last report. Firstly, we organized a successful Partners' Conference in July 2022 – we were pleased to witness a high level of interest and participation and, importantly, commitment from key partners. We contributed to the 2022 and 2023 editions of World Cotton Day celebrations – the commemoration of the day helped to shine a light on the important of cotton to the lives and livelihoods of millions of people across the global and importantly, those who have been adversely impacted by market distortions and pest and infestation.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 5.7-->
                    <paragraph id="5.7">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>Secondly, we started an innovative and action-oriented partnership with FIFA, specifically to support value addition activities in the C-4 and their partner countries as well as to drive value chain development by connecting existing supply with programmes such as football for schools, a FIFA/UNESCO support initiative. This project is already yielding some results which I will come back to a bit later.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 5.8-->
                    <paragraph id="5.8">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>Overall, the trend for cotton development cooperation activities, as recorded in the 10th Periodic Report, is positive in terms of cotton-specific commitments.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 5.9-->
                    <paragraph id="5.9">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>In this connection, I would like to commend all the Members who have provided updates for the latest three revisions of the table, namely: Brazil, Canada, the European Union, France, Italy, Japan, Netherlands, and Thailand.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 5.10-->
                    <paragraph id="5.10">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>I would also like to highlight the important role played by other international organizations that actively collaborate with the WTO with regard to our cotton development assistance mandate, including: Afreximbank, the Common Fund for Commodities (CFC), the United Nations Food and Agriculture Organization (FAO), the International Cotton Advisory Committee (ICAC), the International Trade Centre (ITC), the United Nations Conference on Trade and Development (UNCTAD), the United Nations Industrial Development Organization (UNIDO).</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 5.11-->
                    <paragraph id="5.11">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>Besides recalling here these important contributions, I would like to say a few words on the observance of World Cotton Day 2023, were I participated in-person, as well as on our MoU with FIFA, under the relevant cotton chapter.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 5.12-->
                    <paragraph id="5.12">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>From my experience at World Cotton Day (WCD) 2023 celebrations in Vienna, it is evident that World Cotton Day has established itself as a booster for action in support of the cotton sector, in particular in the C-4, LDCs and other developing countries where cotton is of vital importance for the livelihoods of so many people.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 5.13-->
                    <paragraph id="5.13">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>Discussions with Ministers and Heads of international organizations again confirmed the urgency attached to find a solution to the long-standing issue of the harmful effects linked to distorted cotton markets, and the role that government support plays in this scenario.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 5.14-->
                    <paragraph id="5.14">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>This is made even more urgent by the parallel effects of other factors at play, including:</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 5.15-->
                    <paragraph id="5.15">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>Overall high price volatility, with a mid-term price outlook that does not appear to be particularly encouraging.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 5.16-->
                    <paragraph id="5.16">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>The incidence of pests and other issues that have heavily affected production and exports in the C-4, Côte d'Ivoire and other countries, particularly in Western and Central Africa.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 5.17-->
                    <paragraph id="5.17">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>On the positive side, there is also a genuine intention by the C-4 and their partner countries to invest in sustainable local processing and other value addition activities. Let me be clear, all of these efforts are about delivering for people-people that are far too often left behind. It is about doing our part to create decent jobs particularly for the youth and women, it is about ensuring the economic conditions in cotton producing countries are sufficiently attractive that it helps mitigate the phenomenon of illegal migration and the tragedies that far too often follow.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 5.18-->
                    <paragraph id="5.18">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>I believe this approach by the C-4 and their partner countries is to be strongly supported by members and institutional actors, but also needs the involvement of a broader spectrum of players, including in particular private sector investors.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 5.19-->
                    <paragraph id="5.19">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>This is why I took the initiative, back in September 2022, to enter into an inclusive and dynamic partnership with FIFA, with an MoU that contains a joint engagement to support cotton value addition activities in the C-4 and their partner countries.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 5.20-->
                    <paragraph id="5.20">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>A partnership that has attracted the interest of several actors, including Afreximbank, who matched FIFA's financial support for the conduct of background analytical work under the MoU, but also Better Cotton, ITC and UNIDO, as well as key private sector players. And following on from the last World Cotton both the International Atomic Energy Agency and International Cotton Advisory Centre (ICAC) have requested to join the initiative.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 5.21-->
                    <paragraph id="5.21">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>The objective of integrating cotton from the C-4 and their partner countries into national and continental apparel supply chains linked to football is at the core of this endeavor. Of course, we hope that this will be a catalyst for demand and hope that production and supply of textiles from the C-4 will ultimately go beyond this specific value chain.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 5.22-->
                    <paragraph id="5.22">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>We also believe this can help shine a light on the opportunities for the C-4. Take for example, this year's instalment of WCD brought in the private sector from near and far, interested in exploring how they can participate in the potential of the West African and continental value chain in cotton.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 5.23-->
                    <paragraph id="5.23">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>Connecting C-4 cotton to this 270 billion USD industry would make a material difference to the lives of millions of people in the C-4 and beyond. I understand that steps are already being taken in this direction, first through the football for schools programme and hopefully before too long other categories of actors within this value chain can benefit from supply from high quality production from C-4.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 5.24-->
                    <paragraph id="5.24">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>However, to convert this potential into reality, we need to mobilize investments and strengthen the technical assistance countries receive.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 5.25-->
                    <paragraph id="5.25">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>We also urgently need to support the concrete efforts these countries are making to establish a stable and sustainable business environment at the national and regional levels.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 5.26-->
                    <paragraph id="5.26">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>To that end, the sustained engagement and cooperation of providers of development assistance for cotton, beneficiaries, and partner organizations in the WTO Consultative Framework Mechanism on Cotton is very encouraging.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 5.27-->
                    <paragraph id="5.27">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>It stands as a positive example as we work to consolidate the development dimension of the multilateral trading system.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                </statement_content>
                <!--STATEMENT INFO-->
                <statement_info>
                    <statement_number>5.28</statement_number>
                    <statement>The representative of Cameroon, on behalf of the African Group, delivered the following statement:</statement>
                </statement_info>
                <!--STATEMENT CONTENT-->
                <statement_content>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 5.29-->
                    <paragraph id="5.29">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>The African Group would like to thank you for including this important item on the agenda and express its support for the interventions by the C-4 and Côte d'Ivoire. Cotton farming provides a living for tens of millions of people around the world. Cotton and its by-products are essential to the economies of over 150 countries involved in producing, processing, importing and/or exporting cotton. More specifically, in Africa and particularly for the four co-sponsors of the Sectoral Initiative on Cotton (C-4), cotton plays a key role in the daily lives of the inhabitants of cotton-growing basins, estimated at more than 20 million people, who derive the bulk of their income directly or indirectly from cotton. There is no doubt that, for these countries, it remains a strategic, vital crop that contributes significantly to agricultural production, the economy, trade and employment and provides indisputable leverage in the fight against poverty, particularly in rural areas.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 5.30-->
                    <paragraph id="5.30">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>Cotton trade negotiations have not thus far produced results, despite the many proposals made by the C-4. We believe that MC13 should send a strong signal in terms of the perspectives on cotton at the WTO. The African Group supports the draft decision submitted by the C-4 and Côte d'Ivoire, which seeks to secure a consensual outcome by MC13. Pending the necessary desired developments in terms of trade negotiation outcomes, the African Group would like to call on bilateral and multilateral partners to support the development of cotton farming in Africa in order to contribute not only to structural solutions to constraints that hinder the competitiveness of the African cotton sector, but also to yield improvement and the local processing of cotton and its by-products.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 5.31-->
                    <paragraph id="5.31">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>In view of this, the African Group would like to stress that it is crucial to develop the cotton value chain and manage the various segments thereof. These actions constitute the purpose of the various projects submitted by several cotton-producing African countries, which are eagerly awaiting the necessary funding. They also constitute the purpose of the C-4 draft decision in its development component, which calls on WTO Members to reaffirm previous decisions on cotton and the need for an inclusive partnership, while underscoring the central role of the WTO Consultative Mechanism on Cotton Development Assistance as an international forum of reference.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 5.32-->
                    <paragraph id="5.32">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>The African Group reiterates its commitment to working towards strengthening the multilateral trading system through fair rules and measurable outcomes that will ultimately have a significant impact on the living conditions of millions of people in Africa. The Group calls for more political will and urges WTO Members to continue their efforts to grant African cotton its rightful place in the global markets.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                </statement_content>
                <!--STATEMENT INFO-->
                <statement_info>
                    <statement_number>5.33</statement_number>
                    <statement>The representative of Djibouti, on behalf of the LDC Group, delivered the following statement:</statement>
                </statement_info>
                <!--STATEMENT CONTENT-->
                <statement_content>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 5.34-->
                    <paragraph id="5.34">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>The LDC Group would like to thank the Director-General for her report on the development assistance aspects of the cotton issue and takes note of it. Cotton constitutes one of these products with a systemic and strategic importance in the economies of several LDCs. It is both a basic product as well as an element of subsistence and income for millions of people around the world and particularly in LDCs. We welcome the holding during this year of a range of activities on aspects of the cotton issue relating to development assistance.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 5.35-->
                    <paragraph id="5.35">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>The latest revised version of the Director-General Evolving Table on Cotton Development Assistance revealed that specific aid for cotton exceeded USD 355 million, compared to USD 277 million in the previous revision. However, the supply and demand for cotton on the world market for the 2022/2023 campaign contracted with drops of 2 per cent and 7.55 per cent respectively compared to the previous one. This demonstrates the need to continue supporting cotton farmers in LDCs. In this regard, the LDC Group commends all development partners who have provided support to cotton-producing LDCs through the implementation of different types of development projects.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 5.36-->
                    <paragraph id="5.36">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>Based on the mandates given by Ministers at the MC6 in Hong Kong, at the MC9 in Bali and at the MC10 in Nairobi, the LDC Group calls for an outcome on cotton to correct the imbalances that distort cotton trade on the international market so that cotton producers in LDCs can mainly make a living from their activities by taking better advantage of global value chains.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 5.37-->
                    <paragraph id="5.37">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>In conclusion, the LDC Group urges traditional and non-traditional development partners to support all forms of development initiatives and projects aimed at addressing issues related to the transformation of the cotton sector, the disruption of cotton value chains, the reduction in production and the decline in cotton exports in LDCs.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                </statement_content>
                <!--STATEMENT INFO-->
                <statement_info>
                    <statement_number>5.38</statement_number>
                    <statement>The representative of Chad, on behalf of the C-4, delivered the following statement:</statement>
                </statement_info>
                <!--STATEMENT CONTENT-->
                <statement_content>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 5.39-->
                    <paragraph id="5.39">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>I am making this statement on behalf of the C-4 and the Republic of Côte d'Ivoire, as well as all of the 36 African countries that produce and/or export cotton and its by-products. Allow us to express our deep appreciation to the Secretariat for its ongoing involvement alongside us. We acknowledge the importance and interest of the work carried out on cotton and wish to express our gratitude to all our partners for their valuable support and for helping us to better integrate into the multilateral trading system. Our thanks go to the Director-General for the 10th Periodic Report on the development assistance aspects of cotton.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 5.40-->
                    <paragraph id="5.40">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>The C-4 has followed with great interest the development assistance trends recorded in the Evolving Tables, from the first round of consultations to today. In this regard, the C-4 is pleased to note the positive trends in the 36th updated version of the Evolving Table on Cotton Development Assistance.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 5.41-->
                    <paragraph id="5.41">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>The Evolving Table is a reference tool to monitor trends and trace the evolution of development-assistance projects supporting the cotton sector. The C-4 also welcomes the progress made at the last Partners' Conference to Support Development Assistance for Cotton and the World Cotton Day celebration held on 4 October 2023 in Vienna, Austria.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 5.42-->
                    <paragraph id="5.42">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>However, the C-4 notes the low level of disbursement for some 10-cotton specific development assistance projects. We would also like to point out the unchanging status of the 11 new projects submitted by the C-4 and its members, and by Cameroon and Burundi, almost all of which are still waiting for technical assistance and/or funding for their implementation.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 5.43-->
                    <paragraph id="5.43">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>In light of all these concerns, the C-4 would like to reiterate its Call for Action, urging "WTO Members and multilateral agencies to commit further financial and technical resources, as part of their global development assistance strategies, to allow cotton producing developing countries, in particular the LDCs, to fully exploit the opportunities cotton offers for livelihood improvement, decent work creation and environmentally sustainable value addition".</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 5.44-->
                    <paragraph id="5.44">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>Similarly, the C-4 would like to underscore the importance of its regional and integrative "Cotton Roadmap", the effective implementation of which will create competitive, inclusive and sustainable value chains that are beneficial in terms of the local processing of cotton fibre and capacity-building among stakeholders in the cotton sector.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 5.45-->
                    <paragraph id="5.45">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>We also welcome the launch of the implementation of the Memorandum of Understanding establishing a partnership between the WTO and FIFA, one of the aims of which is to work towards including C-4 and LDC cotton producers in apparel value chains.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 5.46-->
                    <paragraph id="5.46">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>Investment is also still essential to boost production and yields. Coordination among the sector's stakeholders is therefore crucial to increase the value of cotton. There should be technical cooperation on the use of fibre between producer countries and development partners.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 5.47-->
                    <paragraph id="5.47">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>We also believe that access to innovative technologies could help provide cotton producers with the tools they need to increase their yield and, thus, their income.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 5.48-->
                    <paragraph id="5.48">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>We should work to increase the productivity of cotton production systems by arming smallholder cotton farmers with the information they need to grow more and better cotton, minimize the environmental impact and generate more income for their families.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 5.49-->
                    <paragraph id="5.49">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>We recall that cotton allows for the development of value chains, from agricultural research on seeds to its processing into textile products and other by-products. With this in mind and in developing the cotton value chain, our young people will not be tempted by the risky options of migration or rural exodus. Cotton also contributes to guaranteeing peace, dignity and prosperity, and thus to achieving the Sustainable Development Goals.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 5.50-->
                    <paragraph id="5.50">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>For these reasons, we would like to call on all our partners to contribute to the effective implementation of the various projects. The development partners play a key role in our capacity to develop our cotton production, improve its quality, and ensure that our raw output is processed into higher value finished products that can then be exported to various markets.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 5.51-->
                    <paragraph id="5.51">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>Regarding the trade component, I would like to stress that cotton is a crucial sector for us, and tangible outcomes have remained elusive in this area since the launch of the sectoral initiative in 2003.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 5.52-->
                    <paragraph id="5.52">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>We therefore believe that MC13 should send a reassuring message on cotton and that there should be continued fulfilment of the commitments Members made to address cotton "ambitiously, expeditiously and specifically" as part of the agriculture negotiations. To that end, the C-4 has submitted a draft decision on cotton and hopes that a broad consensus will be reached on this draft with a view to its adoption at MC13.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 5.53-->
                    <paragraph id="5.53">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>Before I conclude, I would like to take this opportunity to reiterate the C-4's appreciation for its partners and all actors in the consultation mechanism. The C-4 wishes to express its strong desire to see, in the next version of the Evolving Table, positive developments in support of the various development projects in Africa's cotton sector that still await funding.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                </statement_content>
                <!--STATEMENT INFO-->
                <statement_info>
                    <statement_number>5.54</statement_number>
                    <statement>The representative of Brazil delivered the following statement:</statement>
                </statement_info>
                <!--STATEMENT CONTENT-->
                <statement_content>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 5.55-->
                    <paragraph id="5.55">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>Cotton is of high importance for LDCs, especially for those 30 African countries that produce or trade it. Brazil supports, in the framework of a comprehensive reform of the AoA, an outcome on cotton at the 13th Ministerial Conference. Brazil continues to support LDCs in cotton and cotton-related sectors through the Brazilian Programme to Support the Development of the Cotton Sector in Africa. The Brazilian cooperation aims at increasing cotton productivity and improve fiber quality in 18 African countries. As highlighted by the report, the south-south contribution is a form of cooperation based on solidarity, with shared goals of improving productivity, inclusiveness, and sustainability in the cotton sector.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                </statement_content>
                <!--STATEMENT INFO-->
                <statement_info>
                    <statement_number>5.56</statement_number>
                    <statement>The representative of Paraguay delivered the following statement:</statement>
                </statement_info>
                <!--STATEMENT CONTENT-->
                <statement_content>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 5.57-->
                    <paragraph id="5.57">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>We wish to thank the Director-General for her periodic report and the technical assistance activities carried out to date. There is an urgent need to address the matter of cotton in the agriculture negotiations, across all negotiating pillars. We concur that specific outcomes on cotton can be reached at the next Ministerial Conference as part of a holistic package that meets the needs of the C-4, in a holistic package of agricultural outcomes.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 5.58-->
                    <paragraph id="5.58">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>The cotton sector needs to be reformed urgently, since, as evidenced in the Cairns Group document on concentrations of support, cotton is still one of the most distorted sectors, with its support heavily concentrated among just a few Members. We support the C-4's efforts to create fairer, more equitable and more market-oriented trade in the cotton sector. As proponents of the Cairns Group paper on modalities for domestic support, contained in JOB/AG/243/Rev.1, we are convinced that the alternatives set out therein will further this objective. Lastly, as we did in the CoA SS, we would like to invite the C-4 to work together with us to develop the market access pillar in its future proposals.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                </statement_content>
                <!--STATEMENT INFO-->
