        <!--AGENDA-->
        <agenda>
            <!--AGENDA ITEM, HEADING-->
            <agenda_item>
                <agenda_item_number>8</agenda_item_number>
                <p>
                    <t>WTO PENSION PLAN – AMENDMENT TO THE REGULATIONS (WT/GC/W/906)</t>
                </p>
            </agenda_item>
        </agenda>
        <!--AGENDA-->
        <agenda>
            <!--AGENDA ITEM, HEADING-->
            <agenda_item>
                <agenda_item_number>9</agenda_item_number>
                <p>
                    <t>LDC GRADUATION (ANNEX 2 OF WT/GC/W/807/REV.2) – REPORT BY THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE COMMITTEE ON TRADE AND DEVELOPMENT TO THE GENERAL COUNCIL (WT/COMTD/LDC/30)</t>
                </p>
            </agenda_item>
            <!--OPENING-->
            <opening>
                <!--OPENING, PARAGRAPH 9.1-->
                <p>
                    <t>The Chairperson noted that at the July meeting, the General Council agreed that the Sub-Committee on LDCs would continue the discussion on Annex 2 of the LDC graduation proposal contained in WT/GC/W/807/Rev.2 and to report to the General Council by 30 November 2023 with any recommendations. She then offered the floor to Ambassador José R. Sanchez-Fung (Dominican Republic), the Chairperson of the Committee on Trade and Development, who had been chairing the meetings of the Sub-Committee on LDCs since September 2023, pending the election of the Chairperson of the Sub-Committee on LDCs.</t>
                </p>
            </opening>
            <!--STATEMENT SECTION-->
            <statements>
                <!--STATEMENT INFO-->
                <statement_info>
                    <statement_number>9.2</statement_number>
                    <statement>Ambassador José Sánchez-Fung (Dominican Republic), Chairperson of the Committee on Trade and Development, delivered the following statement:</statement>
                </statement_info>
                <!--STATEMENT CONTENT-->
                <statement_content>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 9.3-->
                    <paragraph id="9.3">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>Following the instruction by the General Council in July this year to examine Annex 2 of the LDC graduation proposal, the LDC Sub-Committee began its work in September. I have provided a succinct summary of the main discussions in my report to the General Council which has been circulated in document WT/COMTD/LDC/30.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 9.4-->
                    <paragraph id="9.4">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>I will not repeat what I have said in my report. I would just like to underline a few points:</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 9.5-->
                    <paragraph id="9.5">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>First, we have tried our best to advance the discussions through informal sessions of the LDC Sub-Committee. We have had five informal meetings and one small group consultation. All the 17 S&amp;D provisions identified by LDCs in Annex 2 were taken up in clusters, and we had a good exchange of views on all the key issues in the proposal ranging from market access to subsidies to intellectual property matters. We now have a better understanding of the background of all the LDC-specific provisions in WTO Agreements and decisions identified in Annex 2.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 9.6-->
                    <paragraph id="9.6">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>Second, the discussions were facilitated by the factual presentations from the Secretariat. I would like to thank the Secretariat for being available at short notice. We have also been reassured that a wide range of technical assistance remains available to graduating LDCs for their effective participation in the system.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 9.7-->
                    <paragraph id="9.7">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>Third, the discussions have been substantive. I would like to thank Members for their positive and constructive engagements. We have covered a lot of ground. At the same time, I believe some further discussion is necessary to better understand the specific challenges of graduating LDCs and to explore possible avenues for support. I would, therefore, like to request the General Council to provide some additional time to the LDC Sub-Committee to further examine the provisions in Annex 2 with a view to making any possible recommendations to the General Council to ensure a smooth transition for graduating LDCs. We can also try to use the limited time we have before MC13 to see whether some progress can be made, for Ministers consideration at MC13.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 9.8-->
                    <paragraph id="9.8">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>Overall, Members remain committed to support the LDCs on their path to graduation. We already achieved an important outcome on Annex 1 during the senior officials meeting in October. And I stand ready to support any process going forward.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                </statement_content>
                <!--STATEMENT INFO-->
                <statement_info>
                    <statement_number>9.9</statement_number>
                    <statement>The representative of Djibouti, on behalf of the LDC Group, delivered the following statement:</statement>
                </statement_info>
                <!--STATEMENT CONTENT-->
                <statement_content>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 9.10-->
                    <paragraph id="9.10">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>The LDC Group thanks the LDC Sub-Committee Chairperson for his report (WT/COMTD/LDC/30) and facilitating the discussion. We are grateful to all delegations for their constructive engagement at the sub-committee. The LDC Group also thanks the Secretariat colleagues for their expert reflections on the Annex 2 listed provisions. Our Group has submitted a document (WT/GC/W/919) to summarize our thoughts on the remaining work on the Annex 2 of the LDC graduation proposal for the consideration of Members.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 9.11-->
                    <paragraph id="9.11">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>As highlighted in the report of the LDC Sub-Committee Chair, we have gone through an in-depth review of the different LDC-specific provisions listed in Annex 2 of our proposal, and explained the rationale for extending them to graduated LDCs for a reasonable period of time.  The LDC-specific provisions in WTO have been approved by the whole membership to respond to the unique vulnerabilities affecting LDCs, and that WTO Members have already recognized that they should equally apply to all LDCs. Since graduation is not changing the inherited challenges overnight, LDC-specific provisions should also be available to Members for some years after their graduation from the LDC category.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 9.12-->
                    <paragraph id="9.12">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>The LDC Group welcomes the GC Decision (WT/L/1172) on Annex-1, as we were about to begin the SOM. The decision constitutes an important first part agreement and has given us the needed momentum toward MC13. The decision on 23 October also addresses several of the market access-related issues listed in Annex 2. Based on these considerations, the LDC Group is ready to review the list of provisions in Annex 2 with a view to reducing those provisions.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 9.13-->
                    <paragraph id="9.13">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>Given the critical importance of this issue for the LDC Group, we must avoid endless debates on questions that have already been answered by the LDC Group. This will delay any action on this second part of the LDC graduation proposal.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 9.14-->
                    <paragraph id="9.14">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>At this stage, Members should first agree on the principle of a transition period, which would apply to the provisions listed in Annex 2 for a fixed number of years. We can therefore ask the LDC Sub-Committee to continue its work as provided in the July 2023 GC meeting and report back to the General Council by 31 January 2024 with precise recommendation to make favourable decision by MC13 in this regard.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 9.15-->
                    <paragraph id="9.15">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>The General Council decision in October on Annex 1, concerning unilateral DFQF preferences, is a clear recognition that a transition period after graduation from the LDC category is crucial. Achieving a successful outcome on Annex 2 will also send a strong signal that the multilateral trade system can be responsive to the needs of its more vulnerable Members.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                </statement_content>
                <!--STATEMENT INFO-->
                <statement_info>
                    <statement_number>9.16</statement_number>
                    <statement>The representative of Bangladesh delivered the following statement:</statement>
                </statement_info>
                <!--STATEMENT CONTENT-->
                <statement_content>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 9.17-->
                    <paragraph id="9.17">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>Bangladesh aligns with the statement by the LDC Group. Our delegation thanks the LDC Sub-Committee Chairperson for his report (WT/COMTD/LDC/30) and his facilitating role while the LDC Sub-Committee examined the Annex 2 of the LDC graduation proposal. Bangladesh also thanks all delegations for their active participation in this exercise aiming a favourable outcome. LDC group's recent submission provides some thoughts and expectations on the remaining works on this important topic.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 9.18-->
                    <paragraph id="9.18">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>At the LDC Sub-Committee, as mandated by the General Council, Members reviewed the different LDC-specific provisions listed in Annex 2 of the LDC proposal, and we explained the rationale for extending them to graduated LDCs for a reasonable period of time. The provisions listed in Annex 2 are existing flexibilities and should equally apply to all LDCs, and we request the same flexibility for some additional years after graduation from LDC category.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 9.19-->
                    <paragraph id="9.19">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>With all Members, Bangladesh welcomes the General Council decision (WT/L/1172) on Annex 1 of our graduation proposal. This decision also follows the MC12 paragraph 5 direction that some WTO measures can play supportive roles to LDCs after graduation. In other words, the General Council decision is a recognition that a transition period after graduation from LDC category is important. As we understood form our discussion at the Sub-Committee, the General Council decision will address several of the market access-related components listed in Annex 2.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 9.20-->
                    <paragraph id="9.20">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>We thank the Sub-Committee Chairperson for recognizing the need of the LDCs and for his suggestion for a little more time to conclude the work. We appreciate this positive spirit. We request the General Council to instruct the LDC Sub-Committee to continue its work, similar to the July 2023 GC decision, and report back to the GC by January 2024, as proposed by the LDC Coordinator, or before the MC13 to help make a favourable decision at the MC13 on Annex 2. The delegation of Bangladesh, along with the LDC Group, looks forward to working constructively with Members on this important file.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                </statement_content>
                <!--STATEMENT INFO-->
                <statement_info>
                    <statement_number>9.21</statement_number>
                    <statement>The representative of Cambodia delivered the following statement:</statement>
                </statement_info>
                <!--STATEMENT CONTENT-->
                <statement_content>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 9.22-->
