                    </paragraph>
                </statement_content>
                <!--STATEMENT INFO-->
                <statement_info>
                    <statement_number>9.27</statement_number>
                    <statement>The representative of Nigeria delivered the following statement:</statement>
                </statement_info>
                <!--STATEMENT CONTENT-->
                <statement_content>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 9.28-->
                    <paragraph id="9.28">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>We welcome the report by the CTD Chairperson. At the outset we wish to associate ourselves with the statement delivered on behalf of the African Group. Paragraph 5 of the MC12 Outcome Document acknowledged the challenges of LDCs including the loss of trade-related international support measures after graduation and recognizes the importance of WTO measures to address those challenges. We reaffirm our support for this proposal because we believe graduated LDCs require support during their transition period to foster stability.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 9.29-->
                    <paragraph id="9.29">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>We thank Members for adopting the Annex 1 decision on Extension of Unilateral Duty Free and Quota Free Preferences in Favour of Countries Graduated from the LDC Category and call on Members to give due consideration to the elements of Annex 2 of the proposal and work towards achieving consensus on this issue at MC13.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                </statement_content>
                <!--STATEMENT INFO-->
                <statement_info>
                    <statement_number>9.30</statement_number>
                    <statement>The representative of Egypt delivered the following statement:</statement>
                </statement_info>
                <!--STATEMENT CONTENT-->
                <statement_content>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 9.31-->
                    <paragraph id="9.31">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>Allow me to extend our sincere appreciation for the comprehensive efforts undertaken by the LDC Group, notably Djibouti, in addressing the trade-related challenges faced by Least Developed Countries (LDCs) post-graduation. Egypt commends the dedication reflected in the proposal for WTO Smooth Transition Measures, particularly Annex 1, aiming to extend preferences in favour of countries graduated from the LDC category.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 9.32-->
                    <paragraph id="9.32">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>We warmly welcome the positive decision to adopt Annex 1, recognizing the imperative role it plays in mitigating the potential adverse impacts of graduation on the socio-economic development of these countries. The extension of preferences over a Number of years, or a period, as outlined in Annex 1, aligns with the principles of a smooth transition, and underscores the commitment to supporting LDCs beyond their graduation.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 9.33-->
                    <paragraph id="9.33">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>In tandem with the adoption of Annex 1, Egypt strongly endorses the significance of Annex 2. The LDC Group's proposal encompasses vital principles, including exempting specific measures from WTO dispute settlement actions and extending LDC-specific flexibilities and technical assistance post-graduation. Egypt firmly believes that adopting Annex 2 is essential in ensuring a sustained and sustainable transition for LDCs, safeguarding their hard-earned progress.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 9.34-->
                    <paragraph id="9.34">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>Recognizing the challenges LDCs face in maintaining development momentum after graduation, Egypt supports the call to instruct the Sub-Committee for Least-Developed Countries to formulate recommendations for support measures. The proposed elements in Annex 2, such as continued access to technical assistance and the exemption from dispute settlement actions, are crucial for fortifying the LDCs' resilience post-graduation.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
