                    <statement>The representative of Cameroon, on behalf of the African Group, delivered the following statement:</statement>
                </statement_info>
                <!--STATEMENT CONTENT-->
                <statement_content>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 9.61-->
                    <paragraph id="9.61">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>The African Group takes note and welcomes the report (WT/COMTD/LDC/30) mandated by the General Council to the LDC Sub-Committee to review Annex 2 of the LDC graduation proposal (WT/GC/W/807/Rev.2). The African Group is following with interest the 17 provisions relating to Special and Differential Treatment (SDT) in the WTO Agreements and Decisions contained in Annex 2, with a view to their inclusion in the smooth transition measures in favor of LDCs after their reclassification.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 9.62-->
                    <paragraph id="9.62">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>The African Group welcomes the decision of the General Council (WT/L/1172) on Annex 1, as we were about to begin the Senior Officials' Meeting. The decision constitutes an important first agreement and has given us the necessary momentum towards MC13. The 23 October decision also addresses several of the market access issues listed in Annex 2. The October General Council decision on Annex 1, regarding unilateral FDSC preferences, is a clear recognition because a transition period after graduation from the LDC category is crucial. Achieving a positive outcome on Annex 2 will also send a strong signal that the multilateral trading system can meet the needs of its most vulnerable Members.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 9.63-->
                    <paragraph id="9.63">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>We have repeatedly stressed that we find it difficult to understand the strong resistance by some Members of this proposal by the LDC Group which will neither affect the economic competitiveness of those Members who continue to oppose it nor grant undue rights to this subset of Members, the majority of whom belong to the African Group. The African Group believes that the difficulties encountered by graduating LDCs in implementing WTO rules and disciplines must continue to be addressed. Much progress has been made, but we believe that a thorough review of the 17 SDT proposals identified in Annex 2 would require additional time with a view to making recommendations to the General Council.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 9.64-->
                    <paragraph id="9.64">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>The upcoming Thirteenth Ministerial Conference could be an opportunity to take another look at the progress made, including the possibility of adopting a Decision to further support LDCs in the process of graduating from this category.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
