                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 9.92-->
                    <paragraph id="9.92">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>The General Council took note of the report by the CTD Chairperson and of the statements made.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                </statement_content>
            </statements>
        </agenda>
        <!--AGENDA-->
        <agenda>
            <!--AGENDA ITEM, HEADING-->
            <agenda_item>
                <agenda_item_number>10</agenda_item_number>
                <p>
                    <t>PROPOSED REVISIONS TO WT/L/452 "PROCEDURES FOR THE CIRCULATION AND DERESTRICTION OF WTO DOCUMENTS" – COMMUNICATION FROM AUSTRALIA; BRAZIL; CANADA; COLOMBIA; COSTA RICA; EUROPEAN UNION; NEW ZEALAND; NORWAY; SWITZERLAND; SEPARATE CUSTOMS TERRITORY OF TAIWAN, PENGHU, KINMEN AND MATSU; THE UNITED KINGDOM AND THE UNITED STATES (WT/GC/W/897/REV.1)</t>
                </p>
            </agenda_item>
            <!--OPENING-->
            <opening>
                <!--OPENING, PARAGRAPH 10.1-->
                <p>
                    <t>The Chairperson said that the following item "Proposed Revisions to WT/L/452 'Procedures for the Circulation and Derestriction Of WTO Documents' – Communication from Australia; Brazil; Canada; Colombia; Costa Rica; European Union; New Zealand; Norway; Switzerland; Separate Customs Territory of Taiwan, Penghu, Kinmen And Matsu; the United Kingdom and the United States (WT/GC/W/897/Rev.1)" had been included in the agenda at the request of the co-sponsors. She further noted that this proposal had been previously discussed at the July General Council meeting. She then invited one of the co-sponsors to provide an update on the item and communication.</t>
                </p>
            </opening>
            <!--STATEMENT SECTION-->
            <statements>
                <!--STATEMENT INFO-->
                <statement_info>
                    <statement_number>10.2</statement_number>
                    <statement>The representative of Canada delivered the following statement:</statement>
                </statement_info>
                <!--STATEMENT CONTENT-->
                <statement_content>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 10.3-->
                    <paragraph id="10.3">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>Thank you for the support this proposal received in July. For those who are new to this proposal, what we have proposed are a series of modest tweaks to the 2002 decision which would build on and enhance the transparency of documents while retaining the right of any Member to keep its own communications restrictions when necessary. It also adds guidance on the WTO website.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 10.4-->
                    <paragraph id="10.4">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>We believe that this decision will help to modernize the WTO and will help external stakeholders to better understand this organization and the work that we undertake here. We hope that the General Council can agree to make these changes and adopt the resulting revised decision.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                </statement_content>
                <!--STATEMENT INFO-->
                <statement_info>
                    <statement_number>10.5</statement_number>
                    <statement>The representative of Chile delivered the following statement:</statement>
                </statement_info>
                <!--STATEMENT CONTENT-->
                <statement_content>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 10.6-->
                    <paragraph id="10.6">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>My delegation thanks the co-sponsors of this draft decision, which seeks to improve the transparency of and open up the work of the Organization. We consider it to be a concrete and practical step in that direction and we are pleased to offer our support.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                </statement_content>
                <!--STATEMENT INFO-->
                <statement_info>
                    <statement_number>10.7</statement_number>
                    <statement>The representative of Antigua and Barbuda, on behalf of the OECS, delivered the following statement:</statement>
                </statement_info>
                <!--STATEMENT CONTENT-->
                <statement_content>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 10.8-->
                    <paragraph id="10.8">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>We thank the proponents for this item. As the proponents have noted, we also perceive the value of increasing ease of access to official WTO documents. This is an important part of enhancing the organization's visibility to the outside world which can have important transparency and credibility dividends. We do believe though, that the proposal requires further reflection so as to avoid unintended consequences and perhaps we need a deeper conversation on many of the recommendations contained in the proposal.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 10.9-->
                    <paragraph id="10.9">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>In principle, we are not against derestriction. However, we also believe that this has to balanced carefully against the confidentiality which some of our work demands. Paragraph 5 of the proposal, for example, could lead to sensitive negotiating documents and positions being exposed to the public prematurely. We perhaps need greater clarity on what types of documents and information are best suited to derestriction. Maybe we can even contemplate a trial basis for certain types of documents with the goal of ultimately arriving at a more comprehensive approach.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                </statement_content>
                <!--STATEMENT INFO-->
                <statement_info>
                    <statement_number>10.10</statement_number>
                    <statement>The representative of China delivered the following statement:</statement>
                </statement_info>
                <!--STATEMENT CONTENT-->
                <statement_content>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 10.11-->
                    <paragraph id="10.11">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>China appreciates the efforts of co-sponsors on putting forward the proposal for the optimization of procedures for the circulation and derestriction of WTO documents. China supports improving the transparency of WTO's daily work, which will help enhance external stakeholders' understanding of the WTO. We are open to the suggestions that all documents relating to agendas or meeting organization could be de-restricted, and meeting minutes could be automatically derestricted 30 days after the date of circulation.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 10.12-->
                    <paragraph id="10.12">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>However, we are not in the position to support the one-size-fits-all approach and are concerned over the potential impact of public access to some sensitive information or documents, for example, members' negotiating positions or materials. China stands ready to further engage with the proponents on this proposal.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                </statement_content>
