                    <statement_number>11.84</statement_number>
                    <statement>The representative of Nigeria delivered the following statement:</statement>
                </statement_info>
                <!--STATEMENT CONTENT-->
                <statement_content>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 11.85-->
                    <paragraph id="11.85">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>We thank Singapore for their proposal. At the outset, we wish to associate ourselves with the statement delivered on behalf of the African Group. Nigeria believes that the WTO should contribute, within its mandate, to address the structural causes of food and livelihood insecurity and unlock Developing Countries Productive capacity. It for this reason that Nigeria under the auspices of the African Group is seeking MC13 outcome that include substantive food security and livelihoods package that would address trade distorting domestic support, especially with regards to levelling the playing field, PSH, SSM and Cotton.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 11.86-->
                    <paragraph id="11.86">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>As indicated by the African Group, the Singapore proposal which is confined to issues of transparency and new disciplines on export restrictions would not address the food security difficulties in Developing Countries. In our view, the current disciplines on Export Restrictions both in the GATT (Article XI) and the AoA (Article 12) is sufficient and balanced to address export restrictions as well as to safeguard policy space when required to address essential food needs of Members in times of critical food shortages. In addition, we are also not in a position to support additional transparency obligations given capacity and resource constraint.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 11.87-->
                    <paragraph id="11.87">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>We therefore call on Singapore to support efforts towards delivering substantive food security and livelihoods package with decisions on issues under negotiations in the CoA SS such as Domestic Support, PSH, SSM, and Cotton at MC13.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                </statement_content>
