                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>We commend China for the proposed declaration and Singapore is pleased to be a co-sponsor. First, this is a timely and forward-looking initiative that provides the political impetus to strengthen regulatory cooperation. It affirms the importance of cooperation and development, and adoption of international standards to reduce regulatory divergence, businesses' compliance costs, and market fragmentation. Second, the proposed Declaration seeks to enhance Members' notification procedures, for example, through the use of digital tools. This will contribute to greater transparency of Members' TBT measures and facilitate cooperation in regulatory development. Third, the draft Declaration also seeks to strengthen the functioning the TBT Committee. Hence, we look forward to the Declaration being adopted at MC13.</t>
                            </p>
