                <!--STATEMENT INFO-->
                <statement_info>
                    <statement_number>13.39</statement_number>
                    <statement>The representative of the United States delivered the following statement:</statement>
                </statement_info>
                <!--STATEMENT CONTENT-->
                <statement_content>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 13.40-->
                    <paragraph id="13.40">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>Like others, we would note that we only received this a couple of days ago, so we are still in the process of reviewing it. I will say that we agree that there is an urgent need to enhance Members agricultural productivity and resiliency, we also agree that there is an urgent need to enhance accessibility of food and we agree that there is a need to enhance transparency of all forms of agricultural trade policy. Of course, the question is how we move from agreeing to those principles to agreeing to tangible outcomes in the agriculture negotiations. Over the past year within the Committee on Agriculture, Members have heard from experts from around the world on the issue of food security and we have discussed Members' own experiences and what we have repeatedly heard from experts was not the need for rolling back WTO rules but rather adherence to the rules and strengthening the rules.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 13.41-->
                    <paragraph id="13.41">
                        <content>
                            <p>
