                    <statement>The Director-General delivered the following statement:</statement>
                </statement_info>
                <!--STATEMENT CONTENT-->
                <statement_content>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 16.93-->
                    <paragraph id="16.93">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>What has struck me are the numerous contributions on agriculture and food security. One advantage is sitting back and listening to all of them. It shows a very strong desire in this Council to have an outcome in this area. If you listen there are quite a few similarities in the proposals that have been put forward, as there are differences as well, and I acknowledge that. I want today, on the 30th anniversary of the conclusion of the Uruguay Round, read a quote because I think it will help us with the issue of agriculture. 30 years ago, one of my predecessors Peter Sutherland, who was the Director-General called the successful conclusion of the Uruguay Round on 15 December 1993, a defining moment in modern economic and political history. He said, "Today the world has chosen openness and cooperation instead of uncertainty and conflict". He was speaking to the TNC at the time. I wanted to read this to you because I think I sense a spirit of cooperation. There is a moment of cooperation where we can come around and try to get an outcome on agriculture that delivers something for the farmers whom we are all concerned about and set forward a path for the future. That is all I want – let us try to do that. I am hopeful now after listening to all of you. Thank you.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
