        <!--AGENDA-->
        <agenda>
            <!--AGENDA ITEM, HEADING-->
            <agenda_item>
                <agenda_item_number>18</agenda_item_number>
                <p>
                    <t>INFORMATION ON INVESTMENT FACILITATION FOR DEVELOPMENT – REQUEST FROM CHILE AND THE REPUBLIC OF KOREA ( JOB/GC/373 )</t>
                </p>
            </agenda_item>
            <!--OPENING-->
            <opening>
                <!--OPENING, PARAGRAPH 18.1-->
                <p>
                    <t>The Chairperson noted the item "Information on Investment Facilitation for Development" has been included in the agenda at the request of Chile and the Republic of Korea and invited one of them to introduce the item and the information contained in JOB/GC/373.</t>
                </p>
            </opening>
            <!--STATEMENT SECTION-->
            <statements>
                <!--STATEMENT INFO-->
                <statement_info>
                    <statement_number>18.2</statement_number>
                    <statement>The representative of Chile delivered the following statement:</statement>
                </statement_info>
                <!--STATEMENT CONTENT-->
                <statement_content>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 18.3-->
                    <paragraph id="18.3">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>I am pleased to present the communication contained in document JOB/GC/373, dated 4 December 2023, submitted by the Republic of Korea and Chile on behalf of 117 WTO Members participating in the Investment Facilitation for Development (IFD) negotiations.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 18.4-->
                    <paragraph id="18.4">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>As indicated in the Agenda of the General Council, and following the transparent, inclusive, and open nature of the IFD initiative, this item has been requested to inform all WTO Members of the following: First, that WTO IFD participants have finalized the English text of the IFD Agreement, after completing its legal review. This text, which was circulated to all WTO Members in document INF/IFD/W/52 on 27 November 2023, constitutes a major achievement for IFD participants; who are currently completing the review of the French and Spanish versions; Second, IFD participants intend to make a request in due course to add the IFD Agreement to Annex 4 of the Marrakesh Agreement Establishing the WTO, that is, as an open-ended plurilateral agreement; participants are still working on when to make the request, if early at MC13, and, Third, to achieve such incorporation, we wish to engage with all WTO Members with a view to garnering consensus for the IFD Agreement to produce its pro-development benefits.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 18.5-->
                    <paragraph id="18.5">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>Let me briefly inform the Membership about key elements and implications of the IFD Agreement: Investment facilitation in the WTO is the natural consequence of the growing inter-dependency between trade and investment, together with their potential for promoting economic growth and development. Attracting not only more, but also more sustainable investment, is fundamental especially for developing and LDC Members to upgrade and diversify their production and exports, develop digital infrastructure, encourage technology transfer and innovation, and facilitating their integration into global value chains. Investment facilitation is then critical especially in the current polycrisis. The focus of the IFD Agreement is not on changing participants' investment policies in substance, but on making such investment policies more transparent and investment-related administrative procedures, more streamlined and efficient.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 18.6-->
                    <paragraph id="18.6">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>According to several surveys, this is where investors and businesses most want to see investment reforms. In that sense, the IFD Agreement can contribute to make the WTO more responsive to the needs of the global economy, governments, as well as domestic and foreign economic operators. Providing special and differential treatment, including technical assistance and support for capacity building, to developing and least-developed country participants is a key component of the IFD Agreement. The IFD Agreement provides that the extent and timing of implementation of its provisions shall be related to the capacities of developing and LDC participants. In addition, developing countries and LDCs have the possibility to undertake a Needs Assessment to be better prepared for implementation, including by identifying capacity building support needs.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 18.7-->
                    <paragraph id="18.7">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>To conclude, we remain fully available to address any questions regarding the IFD Agreement. We invite all WTO Members who have not yet joined to analyze its benefits and be part of our growing number of participants.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                </statement_content>
                <!--STATEMENT INFO-->
                <statement_info>
                    <statement_number>18.8</statement_number>
                    <statement>The representative of Cambodia delivered the following statement:</statement>
                </statement_info>
                <!--STATEMENT CONTENT-->
                <statement_content>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 18.9-->
                    <paragraph id="18.9">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>Let me welcome Armenia and Mali who have just recently joined the Investment Facilitation for Development, called IFD in short. I want to begin by thanking the co-coordinators, Ambassador Dr. Sofía and Ambassador Park and all IFD Participants for their tireless efforts and unshakable commitment towards the IFD from the beginning to this remarkable stage.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 18.10-->
                    <paragraph id="18.10">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>Cambodia takes the floor to acknowledge and appreciate the milestone and significant progress of the negotiations on the IFD Agreement, starting from a joint statement initiative in December 2017 and eventually concluded final text in November 2023. This has been a notable achievement of the negotiation exercise at the WTO. There should be more productive activity like this in the organization. With the negotiations amongst over 110 participating WTO Members at all levels of development, held in a transparent and inclusive manner since September 2020, we believe that the IFD will contribute to creating a more transparent, efficient, and predictable environment to facilitate not only more investment, but also more sustainable investment, as well as to support for our domestic, bilateral, and regional reform efforts.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 18.11-->
                    <paragraph id="18.11">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>As an LDC, Cambodia has participated in the negotiations and will continue to support the IFD Agreement. This is because we are in needs of development for our future prosperity. We take every moment to think and act upon how we can best harvest the benefits from this organization through collective efforts from WTO Membership. We see the IFD as one of the best examples of development goals to attract more investment and firms into the country, create more jobs for local people, strengthen our competitiveness and fully integrate ourselves into the multilateral trading system.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 18.12-->
                    <paragraph id="18.12">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>We are comfortable with the IFD since we will only be required to undertake commitments which is consistent with our development and financial needs or administrative and institutional capabilities. Plus, the special and differential treatment, where technical assistant and capacity building are available to support us in implementing the commitment and obligations.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 18.13-->
                    <paragraph id="18.13">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>Before I conclude, I hope that the IFD will be realized and be one of the deliverables at the MC13 in Abu Dhabi. We welcome and urge more WTO Members to support and joining the IFD so that we can enjoy the benefits from the IFD Agreement.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                </statement_content>
                <!--STATEMENT INFO-->
                <statement_info>
                    <statement_number>18.14</statement_number>
                    <statement>The representative of Nigeria delivered the following statement:</statement>
                </statement_info>
                <!--STATEMENT CONTENT-->
                <statement_content>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 18.15-->
                    <paragraph id="18.15">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>We wish to associate ourselves with the statement delivered by Chile and the Republic of Korea on this issue. In July, a vast majority of Members concluded negotiations on the text of the Agreement on Investment Facilitation for Development. The conclusion of the negotiations on this commercially meaningful agreement demonstrate that the WTO can indeed deliver results that would foster inclusive growth, create more jobs, and widen the circle of prosperity. This is a remarkable achievement that should be celebrated by all Members as the economic benefits for parties and non-parties are unambiguous.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 18.16-->
                    <paragraph id="18.16">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>The IFD agreement is such that would foster closer international cooperation at the global level and create a more transparent, efficient, and predictable environment that will underpin cross-border flow of investment for the development. We believe it would complement our ongoing efforts towards unlocking opportunities in our economy. We are also of the view that the WTO should be responsive to the economic priorities of its members in this 21st century for the institution to remain relevant. MC13 should recognize this remarkable achievement and set in motion the process of integrating the Agreement on Investment Facilitation for Development into the WTO legal architecture.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 18.17-->
                    <paragraph id="18.17">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>In conclusion, we wish to seize this opportunity to congratulate all those that worked tirelessly over the last six years towards the conclusion of the negotiations especially the co-coordinators of the Joint Initiative.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                </statement_content>
                <!--STATEMENT INFO-->
                <statement_info>
                    <statement_number>18.18</statement_number>
                    <statement>The representative of El Salvador delivered the following statement:</statement>
                </statement_info>
                <!--STATEMENT CONTENT-->
                <statement_content>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 18.19-->
                    <paragraph id="18.19">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>Regarding the agenda item, I would like to thank Ambassador Boza and express my support for her statement on the current status and next steps of the Agreement on Investment Facilitation for Development. We also recognize and appreciate the leadership of both co-coordinators and their tireless work and dedication.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 18.20-->
                    <paragraph id="18.20">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>I would like to focus on the benefits that this type of agreement will offer developing countries and small economies like El Salvador, including its contribution to job creation, technology transfer and the expansion and diversification of productive capacity and trade. The Agreement is aimed at enhancing transparency and streamlining investment-related processes, making it easier for developing countries to participate in global investment flows and thus promoting sustainable economic growth.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 18.21-->
                    <paragraph id="18.21">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>For this reason, we support the call by the co-coordinators and the more than 100 proponents of this joint initiative, including 80 developing Members, to incorporate the Agreement into the WTO architecture in a timely manner so that the expected benefits of its implementation can be delivered. Lastly, we would like to invite other Members to support the Agreement.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                </statement_content>
                <!--STATEMENT INFO-->
                <statement_info>
                    <statement_number>18.22</statement_number>
                    <statement>The representative of Honduras delivered the following statement:</statement>
                </statement_info>
                <!--STATEMENT CONTENT-->
                <statement_content>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 18.23-->
                    <paragraph id="18.23">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>I would like to take this opportunity to thank the co-coordinators for their leadership and guidance. The IFD Agreement is the product of the diligent and valuable work of 117 Members on this issue, which is so important for sustainable development. This milestone marks a significant step towards smoother and fairer trade among nations. We welcome the conclusion of the legal review of the English text, as well as the ongoing work in Spanish and French.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 18.24-->
                    <paragraph id="18.24">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>We urge Members to demonstrate the will and flexibility to build the political momentum needed to add the IFD Agreement to Annex 4, and thus attract and retain higher quality investment, taking into account the respective development priorities of Members and fostering a business climate more conducive to sustainable development.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                </statement_content>
                <!--STATEMENT INFO-->
                <statement_info>
                    <statement_number>18.25</statement_number>
                    <statement>The representative of Cameroon delivered the following statement:</statement>
                </statement_info>
                <!--STATEMENT CONTENT-->
                <statement_content>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 18.26-->
                    <paragraph id="18.26">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>I am making this statement in my national capacity. I would like to begin by thanking Chile and the Republic of Korea for including this item on our work agenda in the General Council and for the information provided on investment facilitation for development. Cameroon is a developing country that is deeply committed to the structural transformation of its economy. This is also the rationale behind our bid to host MC14, for which a number of our friends here in the room who are leaving us will be on the special guest list.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 18.27-->
                    <paragraph id="18.27">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>The joint initiative on investment facilitation is a powerful vehicle for boosting development. By way of example, streamlining and speeding up investment procedures or strengthening frank dialogue between the Government and investors are key. I am pleased to announce that my country has decided to join this relevant initiative in the near future. Lastly, my delegation commends the leadership of Ambassador Li Chenggang and his country in promoting the initiative.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                </statement_content>
                <!--STATEMENT INFO-->
                <statement_info>
                    <statement_number>18.28</statement_number>
                    <statement>The representative of Liberia delivered the following statement:</statement>
                </statement_info>
                <!--STATEMENT CONTENT-->
                <statement_content>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 18.29-->
                    <paragraph id="18.29">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>Liberia wishes to reiterate its support incorporating the Investment Facilitation for Development Agreement into Annex 4 of the Marrakesh Agreement. As an LDC, attracting foreign direct investment and fostering economic growth pose unique challenges. We firmly believe the IFD Agreement will enable us to harness the advantages of the multilateral trading system and will be a blueprint that will ultimately pave the way for sustainable development. Liberia and other LDCs stand to gain significantly from the IFD Agreement's focus on transparency, streamlined procedures, and efficient administration, increase transparency in investment procedures, streamline bureaucratic hurdles, open up avenues for opportunities, especially for Members with limited trade activity.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 18.30-->
                    <paragraph id="18.30">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>While implementing the IFD Agreement may at first sight present challenges, it is not just a hurdle to overcome; it is a springboard for progress to showcase our national commitment to reform. Successful implementation will not only demonstrate Liberia's commitment to stability, but also unlock its potential to attract investments that spur economic growth and job creation, further bolstering its reputation as a trustworthy and reliable trade partner. Therefore, we call on all Members to join us in endorsing the incorporation of the IFDA Agreement into Annex 4 of the Marrakesh Agreement at the upcoming 13th Ministerial Conference (MC13). This crucial step will unlock its transformative potential and make the final Ministerial Decision by consensus.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                </statement_content>
                <!--STATEMENT INFO-->
                <statement_info>
                    <statement_number>18.31</statement_number>
                    <statement>The representative of Brazil delivered the following statement:</statement>
                </statement_info>
                <!--STATEMENT CONTENT-->
                <statement_content>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 18.32-->
                    <paragraph id="18.32">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>Let me start by thanking Chile and the Republic of Korea for submitting the communication on the Investment Facilitation for Development as co-coordinators of the JSI and on behalf of all participants of the initiative. We align with statements of Chile and the Republic of Korea and commend the leadership of Ambassadors Sofía Boza and Jung Sung Park in guiding the negotiations of the IFD Agreement to its integral conclusion, after the conclusion of the process of legal review last November.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 18.33-->
                    <paragraph id="18.33">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>Investment facilitation lies at the center of Brazil's approach both to international investment agreements, since we developed our model of Cooperation and Investment Facilitation Agreements in 2012, as an alternative to the traditional BIT model focused on investment protection disciplines and the ISDS mechanism. Since 2015, Brazil has signed 14 bilateral and regional investment agreements with trading partners from developing and least developed countries. Investment facilitation has also been a driving force behind domestic reforms, implemented over the last years, to improve the transparency, predictability, and efficiency of our business and investment climate.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 18.34-->
                    <paragraph id="18.34">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>Based on our domestic experience with investment facilitation agreements and reforms, as well as findings from international organizations and academia, we firmly believe that the disciplines contained in the IFD Agreement will contribute to increase FDI flows to developing and least developed countries that promote job creation, economic growth, integration into regional and global value chains, and ultimately help to achieve the Sustainable Development Goals. We are of the view that the centrality of the development dimension in the JSI on IFD is, to a large extent, a result of the active role played by developing countries throughout the negotiations as coordinators, small group facilitators, and proponents.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 18.35-->
                    <paragraph id="18.35">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>The development dimension of the IFD Agreement is reflected in the inclusion of a robust set of Special and Differential Treatment (SDT) and Technical Assistance and Capacity Building provisions, which provides flexibility and support needed by developing and least developed Members for the implementation of the agreement, and also in the strong commitment of participants and IOs to support the ongoing process of Investment Facilitation Needs assessment.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 18.36-->
                    <paragraph id="18.36">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>We strongly believe that the incorporation of the IFD Agreement to Annex 4 of the Marrakesh Agreement as soon as possible will show that the WTO can deliver agreements that bring social and economic benefits to governments, businesses and citizens of the developing and least developed members of this Organization, while placing the development dimension at the center of its efforts. Brazil calls on all Members to support the legal incorporation of the IFD Agreement and looks forward to engaging on constructive discussions on how we can achieve this objective.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                </statement_content>
                <!--STATEMENT INFO-->
