                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 18.93-->
                    <paragraph id="18.93">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>After six years of intensive and productive work, we now have a consensus text of the Investment Facilitation for Development Agreement. The Agreement is a valuable tool, with the potential to facilitate foreign investment flows between countries. The support from the WTO Secretariat and the harmonious work of Ambassador Boza of Chile and Ambassador Park of Korea are exemplary and have paved the way for endorsement by 117 WTO Members. The Agreement will make it possible to implement innovative provisions, improving the levels of transparency and predictability of measures, streamlining and speeding up procedures to facilitate investment, and enhancing cross-border cooperation, information sharing and the adoption of best practices. It also includes the promotion of sustainable development as a means to encourage the uptake by investors and enterprises of responsible practices. Special and differential treatment is an essential element of the Agreement, including technical assistance and support for capacity building. Foreign investment is an important factor for economic and social development, contributing to poverty reduction, job creation, technology transfer, as well as the expansion and diversification of productive capacity and trade. For that reason, we are excited about the expected benefits of the Agreement, especially for developing and least developed countries.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
