                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>I would like to thank Members for their comments, notwithstanding the different views. The active engagement by Members on this item demonstrates a common desire to make trade and environment mutually supportive, and a strong will for an outcome on trade and environment at MC13. An outcome that builds on progress made since MC12, an outcome that provides concrete guidance to our future work up to MC14 and an outcome that is conducive to turn multilateral discussions into collective and cooperative trade actions. As I already mentioned, the global environmental challenges are real. MC13 is an opportunity that we cannot afford to miss. China would like to work with all Members to strive for balanced and meaningful outcomes on trade and environment at MC13.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
