                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>China is pleased to see that the 57th Session of Joint Advisory Group of ITC/UNCTAD/WTO was successfully held. And we commend ITC's efforts on supporting MSMEs growth and helping developing members achieve economic recovery. China cherishes the cooperative relationship with ITC. Since the first China International Import Expo (CIIE) held in 2018, ITC has organized 325 MSMEs from more than 30 members to participate in the event. Their participation has generated businesses of around 65 million US dollars in total.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
                    <!--STATEMENT PARAGRAPH 22.25-->
                    <paragraph id="22.25">
                        <content>
                            <p>
                                <t>Furthermore, ITC and WTO collaboration on trade has been very fruitful for development and inclusiveness purposes. For example, ITC help businesses like MSMEs understand, adapt to and benefit from trade rules. It also contributes to the topic of women empowerment by implementing programs facilitating women entrepreneurs. It collaborates with WTO on trade facilitation, in particular through the WTO Trade Facilitation Agreement Facility. Its work on Investment Facilitation for Development is very solid. By implementing "Fostering Knowledge and A Common Understanding on Investment Facilitation Project", the ITC strengthens the capacity of developing and least developed members of participating in the WTO negotiations on IFD Agreement through a series of regional seminars and workshops, and also supports members conducting investment facilitation self-assessment through experience sharing. Next year, ITC will celebrate its 60th anniversary. China looks forward to deepening the cooperation with ITC and its work with the WTO.</t>
                            </p>
                        </content>
                    </paragraph>
