        <!--AGENDA-->
        <agenda>
            <!--AGENDA ITEM, HEADING-->
            <agenda_item>
                <agenda_item_number>23</agenda_item_number>
                <p>
                    <t>REVIEW OF WTO ACTIVITIES</t>
                </p>
            </agenda_item>
            <!--OPENING-->
            <opening>
                <!--OPENING, PARAGRAPH 23.1-->
                <p>
                    <t>The Chairperson took up the reports listed under item 23, which had been prepared in line with the Decision concerning Procedures for an Annual Overview of WTO Activities and for Reporting under the WTO (WT/L/105). Delegations had already had substantive discussions on these reports in the respective bodies where they had already been adopted, and therefore the Chairperson suggested not to repeat those discussions in the General Council. She also noted that, in line with the reporting obligations, reports from the respective bodies would be forwarded to the Ministerial Conference. She proposed that, in accordance with practice, the General Council took action on these reports. She therefore invited the General Council to adopt the report of the Committee on Trade and Development in document WT/COMTD/103, and to take note of the reports of the other WTO bodies, including the reports of the Committees under the Plurilateral Trade Agreements, listed in the Proposed Agenda.</t>
                </p>
                <!--OPENING, PARAGRAPH 23.2-->
                <p>
                    <t>The General Council so agreed.</t>
                </p>
                <!--OPENING, PARAGRAPH 23.3-->
                <p>
                    <t>The Chairperson then proposed that the General Council adopt the draft Report of the General Council contained in document WT/GC/W/907, on the understanding that the Secretariat would make the necessary adjustments to that Report to include matters that have been considered at this meeting. The Annual Report of the General Council would then be forwarded to the Ministerial Conference.</t>
                </p>
                <!--OPENING, PARAGRAPH 23.4-->
                <p>
                    <t>The General Council so agreed.</t>
                </p>
            </opening>
        </agenda>
        <!--AGENDA-->
        <agenda>
            <!--AGENDA ITEM, HEADING-->
            <agenda_item>
                <agenda_item_number>24</agenda_item_number>
                <p>
                    <t>APPOINTMENT OF OFFICERS TO WTO BODIES – ANNOUNCEMENT BY THE CHAIRPERSON PURSUANT TO PARAGRAPH 7.1(A) OF THE GUIDELINES (WT/L/510)</t>
                </p>
            </agenda_item>
            <!--OPENING-->
            <opening>
                <!--OPENING, PARAGRAPH 24.1-->
                <p>
                    <t>The Chairperson recalled that the relevant Guidelines provided that the outgoing General Council Chairperson would conduct consultations on the Appointment of Chairpersons to the WTO Bodies in Groups 1, 2, 4 and 5 of its Annex. Given the busy period ahead, she noted that she had initiated this process already on 6 November. In accordance with the Guidelines, she had been assisted in this process by Ambassador Petter Ølberg (Norway), Chairperson of the Dispute Settlement Body, and Ambassador Dacio Castillo (Honduras), former Chairperson of the General Council. A list of past Chairpersons of major bodies was made available to delegations at this meeting. The Chairperson said that, in accordance with the Guidelines, representatives of Members in financial arrears for over one full year could not be considered for appointment.</t>
                </p>
                <!--OPENING, PARAGRAPH 24.2-->
                <p>
                    <t>The Chairperson informed Members that she had first met on 9 November with the four group coordinators – (i) Africa, (ii) Asia and the Pacific; (iii) Latin America and the Caribbean, and (iv) developed countries. As announced in her communication on 9 November, she had requested group coordinators to communicate their expressions of interest by 6 December. She had met group coordinators again on Friday, 8 December, and was pleased to note that there was an emerging draft slate of names.</t>
                </p>
                <!--OPENING, PARAGRAPH 24.3-->
                <p>
                    <t>She said her intention was to send a communication to all Members before the end-of-year break containing the draft slate of names with a view to preparing the ground for an informal General Council meeting in the New Year to finalize the slate of names as early as possible in 2024. She added that this way, Members were on track to complete the shared objective of finalizing the crucially important housekeeping function and, in doing so, ensure a smooth conduct of WTO bodies in 2024.</t>
                </p>
                <!--OPENING, PARAGRAPH 24.4-->
                <p>
                    <t>The General Council took note of the Chairperson's statement.</t>
                </p>
            </opening>
        </agenda>
        <!--AGENDA-->
        <agenda>
